http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Jatha-marks-Vivekananda-birth-anniversary/article13996144.ece

Minister for Textiles and Ports Baburao Chinchansur flagged off a jatha from the Deputy Commissioner’s office to the Vidhya Mangal Bhavan here on Tuesday, to mark the 153rd birth anniversary of Swami Vivekananda.K. Chandrashekhar, Deputy Director of Public Instruction, who inaugurated the programme organised by the Kannada and Culture Department at the Vidhya Mangala Bhavan, said that Swami Vivekananda’s thoughts were always inspiring to people, particularly the youth.Today’s youth should adopt Vivekananda’s ideals to build a healthy nation, he said.Vivek BandThe Bharatiya Janata Party (BJP) too celebrated the Swami’s birth anniversary.Shanarabhupal Reddy, BJP’s district unit president, who inaugurated a campaign, Vivek Band, said that the campaign will be carried out till January 26. The party will distribute bands to students in schools and colleges urging them to follow the principles adopted by Swami Vivekananda to ensure integration of the nation.S.B. Nadekar, district conveyer of Vivek Band, was present.